\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 56. L. glauca} (L.) Chaz., {\i Dict. Jard., Suppl}.{\b  2}: 39 (1790). Annual or perennial, glabrous or glandular-puberulent in inflorescence; stems 5-25 cm, usually several, procumbent to ascending-erect. Leaves 5-15 × 0·3-1 mm, linear, verticillate below, alternate above. Racemes with 3-7 flowers, rather lax, glabrous or glandular-pubescent; pedicels 1-4 mm, shorter or longer than bracts. Corolla 7-14 mm, yellow, rarely with bluish veins; spur 3-8 mm, stout. Capsule 3·5-5 mm, globose. Seeds 1·2-2·5 mm; disc black. •{\i  C. & E. Spain.} Hs.
