\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 59. L. satureioides} Boiss.,{\i  Voy. Bot. Midi Esp.}{\b  2}: 463 (1841). Glandular-pubescent at least in inflorescence; stems 5-25 cm, branched. Leaves 5-15(-25) × 0·5-1·2 mm, linear, verticillate below, alternate above. Racemes with 4-10 flowers, lax; pedicels 2·5-7 mm, longer than bracts. Corolla 8-14 mm, lilac with violet veins; spur 4-7 mm. Capsule 2-4 mm, globose. Seeds 1-1·7 mm, strongly concavo-convex; disc blackish, smooth; wing broad or narrow, white.{\i  Stony or sandy ground; calcicole. • S. Spain, S. Portugal.} Hs Lu.
\par

